headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had 26 points and 11 assists to help the Miami Heat hold off the Boston Celtics 130-124 Sunday as the teams fight for position in the tight Eastern Conference playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler strong down stretch, Heat hold off Celtics 130-124

events.name: New York Knicks at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Derrick Rose scored 25 points off the bench, Reggie Bullock added 24 and the New York Knicks beat the Los Angeles Clippers 106-100 on Sunday to snap an eight-game skid at Staples Center.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Clippers 106-100 behind Rose and Bullock

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Eric Bledsoe had 24 points and 11 assists, Jaxson Hayes added 18 points and the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans stayed alive in the race for the play-in tournament with 112-110 come-from-behind victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans beat Hornets 112-110 to keep play-in hopes alive

headlines.description: — Tim Hardaway Jr. scored 25 points and Josh Richardson had 20, allowing the playoff-bound Dallas Mavericks to overcome the ejection of Luka Doncic in a 124-97 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic ejected in Mavericks' 124-97 victory over Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns and D’Angelo Russell each scored 27 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves built a 30-point halftime lead, led by 43 in the third quarter and cruised to a 128-96 rout of the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Russell each score 27 points, T-Wolves throttle Magic

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 29 points and 16 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls kept their play-in chances alive with an 108-94 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic's double-double, LaVine's 30 lead Bulls over Pistons

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers
Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Maurice Harkless and Terence Davis each scored 18 points to lead eight Sacramento players in double figures, and the Kings beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 126-98 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings spread the scoring, crush Thunder 126-98
